WEBVTT

00:29.346 --> 00:30.627
Welcome to God Day.

00:31.348 --> 00:34.671
I'm Pastor Derek Walker from the Oxford Bible Church.

00:35.432 --> 00:39.876
And I want to share with you today a message called Anointed for Burial.

00:40.677 --> 00:46.983
And this is the key event, I believe, that is the opening of what we call Passion Week.

00:47.003 --> 00:49.486
Now, Passion Week, Passion means suffering, actually.

00:49.546 --> 00:57.714
So this is the week of Christ's death and resurrection.

00:58.082 --> 01:07.015
What had happened in John chapter 11, because we're going to look in John chapter 12, in John chapter 11, Jesus had raised Lazarus from the dead.

01:07.035 --> 01:12.604
And that caused such a stir because it was a real proof that he was the Messiah.

01:13.866 --> 01:20.375
And so he went away for a few weeks out of danger because they were out to kill him.

01:21.357 --> 01:27.506
And in fact, the miracle of Lazarus's resurrection, that's when they decided for sure they were going to.

01:27.938 --> 01:29.059
have him put to death.

01:29.920 --> 01:41.955
And so Jesus went away for a time until the time that God had ordained for him to die, which is at Passover because he was to die as our Passover lamb.

01:42.896 --> 01:57.554
Passover is the feast that pictures our salvation because in the original Passover in Exodus, the destroying angel, the wrath of God was coming through to kill all the firstborn.

01:57.666 --> 02:01.753
And God said, there is only one way of salvation.

02:02.314 --> 02:05.340
And that is the blood of the Lamb, the blood of the Passover Lamb.

02:05.400 --> 02:17.722
And although the Israelites that put the blood of the Lamb on their doors, it says that the Lord hovered over them and protected them.

02:18.283 --> 02:21.970
And so the destroying angel passed them by.

02:22.402 --> 02:36.083
And this is a wonderful picture of salvation, of course, because if we believe in the blood of the Passover lamb and declare our faith in the blood of Jesus, then the wrath of God does not come upon us.

02:36.163 --> 02:43.515
We are protected from the wrath of God because the Passover lamb Jesus himself has borne our wrath for us.

02:43.635 --> 02:50.866
And 1 Corinthians 5, 7 says, Jesus, our Passover lamb has been sacrificed for us.

02:51.074 --> 03:09.741
Thank God for the Passover lamb, but now this is the key moment now that in fact in Exodus 12 it says that the Passover lamb, the story if you like of the Passover lamb begins on the 10th of Nizan.

03:11.023 --> 03:18.514
That is he's to be offered up on the 14th of Nizan, but he is to be set apart

03:19.042 --> 03:20.544
out on the 10th of Nizan.

03:20.584 --> 03:21.905
He had to be without blemish.

03:22.746 --> 03:26.570
And on the 10th of Nizan, he's to be set apart for sacrifice.

03:26.591 --> 03:32.277
And in those days, they would make sure that he was without blemish.

03:32.777 --> 03:35.140
And then he would be sacrificed on the 14th.

03:35.821 --> 03:47.474
And so what we're looking at today, the start of the passion week is when Jesus now officially rides, comes

03:48.130 --> 03:53.057
to present himself for sacrifice as our Passover lamb.

03:53.477 --> 04:00.187
As I say, he'd been in a safe place called Ephraim out of reach of the authorities for a number of weeks.

04:00.988 --> 04:08.859
But now he comes to Bethany, just next door to Jerusalem, right into the danger zone.

04:09.440 --> 04:13.445
And he knows that they are out to kill him.

04:13.466 --> 04:16.690
And so he comes and

04:16.930 --> 04:22.237
What we're looking at now in John chapter 12 is the opening of Passion Week.

04:22.257 --> 04:23.538
This is where it all begins.

04:24.239 --> 04:28.925
And the action begins with him being anointed for burial.

04:30.106 --> 04:37.535
And it's interesting that the next morning is the triumphal entry.

04:38.617 --> 04:39.858
We read that in verse 12.

04:39.918 --> 04:42.962
He goes and presents himself to Israel.

04:43.266 --> 04:51.378
Yes, as her king, but also he is also offering himself to Israel as the Passover lamb for their salvation.

04:52.119 --> 04:54.683
And that was on the 10th of Nizan.

04:55.243 --> 05:02.674
And for the next few days, they tested him, they interrogated him, and he proved himself to be without blemish.

05:02.714 --> 05:05.658
And then he was sacrificed as the Passover lamb.

05:06.480 --> 05:10.866
And so we often think of Palm Sunday, but actually,

05:10.978 --> 05:12.260
It was Palm Monday.

05:13.181 --> 05:17.126
It couldn't have been Palm Sunday because the day before would have been the Sabbath.

05:17.427 --> 05:24.116
And we see that on the day before, Jesus was traveling and it was wrong to travel on the Sabbath.

05:24.156 --> 05:26.178
So we're going to pick up the story here.

05:27.780 --> 05:33.128
In John chapter 12, it says, then six days before the Passover, six days before.

05:33.408 --> 05:39.216
Now, if you count inclusively back from the Friday, that will take you to the Sunday.

05:40.037 --> 05:40.978
And so

05:41.058 --> 06:09.586
Jesus traveled on the Sunday with the other pilgrims up from Jericho up that steep route and arrived at Bethany near the evening time and then it was he was given a supper in his honor at in Bethany and at this supper something amazing happened that Jesus said was so important it should be recorded

06:09.698 --> 06:15.026
for everyone to hear as a memorial whenever the gospel is preached.

06:15.707 --> 06:21.195
And so this is a truly important event at the opening of the Passion Week.

06:21.215 --> 06:22.657
So let's have a look at that.

06:22.777 --> 06:27.624
It says, then six days before the Passover, as I said, this is a Sunday evening.

06:28.205 --> 06:37.298
Jesus came to Bethany where Lazarus who had been dead, where Lazarus was, who had been dead, whom he had raised from the dead.

06:37.762 --> 06:40.246
And there they made him a supper and Martha served.

06:40.706 --> 06:43.751
And Lazarus was one of those who sat at table with him.

06:44.151 --> 06:52.563
Then Mary took a pound of very costly oil of spike nard, anointed the feet of Jesus and wiped his feet with her hair.

06:53.024 --> 06:55.728
And the house was filled with the fragrance of the oil.

06:56.569 --> 07:01.716
And so we see Mary do a beautiful thing here by anointing Jesus.

07:01.776 --> 07:05.682
And we're going to look into the significance of this because

07:05.762 --> 07:13.229
She knew, you see, that Jesus was, he had talked about, but he would suffer and die and rise again.

07:14.070 --> 07:21.237
And she was led by the Holy Spirit to anoint Jesus, to set him apart for burial.

07:21.898 --> 07:25.101
And this is the opening of the Passion Week.

07:26.142 --> 07:33.810
And so it says that in John 11 to this incident,

07:33.954 --> 07:39.662
of Mary anointing Jesus was actually well known already when John wrote his gospel.

07:39.702 --> 07:43.768
He wrote his gospel a bit later than the other three gospel writers.

07:44.369 --> 07:47.834
And so he didn't usually repeat stuff from the other gospels.

07:49.577 --> 07:55.966
Occasionally he did, if it was especially important, but normally he would just add in extra details and clarification.

07:56.026 --> 07:58.930
And so it was already well known.

07:59.042 --> 08:01.464
about this famous incident of Mary.

08:02.245 --> 08:10.112
And in fact, in John 11.2 it says, talking about the story of Lazarus being raised from the dead.

08:10.473 --> 08:19.361
It was that Mary, he said, who anointed the Lord with fragrant oil and wiped his feet with her hair, whose brother Lazarus was sick.

08:19.902 --> 08:25.607
And so he's appealing to what they already knew, only now he's revealing who this woman was.

08:25.967 --> 08:29.010
It was Mary of Bethany, who did this

08:29.314 --> 08:42.088
act of worship and so we can go now to the other gospels to see how they describe this this incident and that gives us a bit more information.

08:42.408 --> 08:58.706
Matthew 26 verse 6 it says and when Jesus was in Bethany at the house of Simon the leper that's where this was a leper that had been healed and who lived in Bethany and so the meal was at their house and then a woman

08:58.914 --> 08:59.635
came to him.

09:00.035 --> 09:10.387
Again, we know this is Mary, having an alabaster flask of very costly fragrant oil, and she poured it on his head as he sat at the table.

09:10.787 --> 09:18.856
Now, John says that he, she poured it on his feet, but here we see it was also poured on his head.

09:19.857 --> 09:24.082
And in Mark 14, 3, it says, then she broke the flask

09:24.322 --> 09:26.284
and poured it out on his head.

09:26.524 --> 09:27.245
She broke it.

09:27.325 --> 09:30.188
She just smashed it and poured it all out on Jesus.

09:31.389 --> 09:47.746
And then it says, again, going back to Matthew in verse eight, it says, but when his disciples saw it, they were indignant saying, why this waste for this fragrant oil might have been sold for much and given to the poor.

09:48.246 --> 09:52.050
But when Jesus was aware of it, he said to them, why do you trouble the woman?

09:53.602 --> 10:03.873
She said, he said, for she has done a good work for me, for you have the poor with you always, but me, you do not have always for in pouring this fragrant oil on my body.

10:04.314 --> 10:06.136
She did it for my burial.

10:06.777 --> 10:18.450
So notice she didn't just pour it on his head and on his feet, but on this whole body, she just threw it all this, this beautiful fragrance covered Jesus with it.

10:20.131 --> 10:22.514
And he says, she did it for my burial.

10:23.682 --> 10:31.395
Surely I say to you, wherever this gospel is preached in the whole world that what this woman has done will also be told as a memorial to her.

10:32.016 --> 10:39.969
Then one of the 12 called Judas Iscariot went to the 12 priests and said, what are you willing to give me if I deliver him to you?

10:39.989 --> 10:44.877
And that's when he made his plan to betray Jesus.

10:44.917 --> 10:48.763
We'll see why Judas was provoked by this incident.

10:49.665 --> 10:50.546
And that's why

10:50.882 --> 10:52.684
Again, we're at the start of Passion Week.

10:52.704 --> 10:58.733
This triggers Judas to betray Jesus, which ultimately leads to his death.

10:59.614 --> 11:08.987
So going back to John now, let's just notice, this is a wonderful picture of Jesus in the house of his friends.

11:09.708 --> 11:11.711
And these are pictures of true believers.

11:12.432 --> 11:17.018
First of all, a true believer is washed and welcoming.

11:18.179 --> 11:18.740
Praise God.

11:19.201 --> 11:20.082
In other words,

11:20.866 --> 11:23.169
We look at Simon, the cleansed leper.

11:23.209 --> 11:26.113
He was a man who had leprosy.

11:26.133 --> 11:29.358
This is a picture of sin and a terrible infection.

11:29.918 --> 11:35.646
And you weren't healed of leprosy so much as you were cleansed from leprosy because it's a picture of sin.

11:36.047 --> 11:39.651
And so he had been cleansed by Jesus.

11:39.732 --> 11:40.933
And that's a picture of us.

11:41.334 --> 11:44.778
We are all forgiven sinners who have been cleansed by Jesus.

11:45.139 --> 11:50.386
And as a result, Simon opened his heart and his home to welcome

11:50.498 --> 11:55.123
to welcome people and to welcome Jesus in particular.

11:55.183 --> 12:07.056
And so when we are these washed forgiven sinners, we open up our heart and our lives to receive Jesus and have fellowship with Jesus.

12:07.536 --> 12:11.901
And of course, Jesus is the Lord's people as well.

12:12.842 --> 12:16.626
And the second person we see is Martha, who was serving

12:17.954 --> 12:23.361
And again, whenever we see Martha, she's busy, she's serving, she's rolling up her sleeves and helping.

12:23.381 --> 12:28.968
And that's another picture of a true believer who's always willing to serve, praise God.

12:29.448 --> 12:31.090
And then we see Lazarus.

12:32.552 --> 12:41.743
In fact, in verse 9 to 11 of John 12, we read this because Lazarus is a picture of a witnessing disciple.

12:41.843 --> 12:43.986
He had just had an outstanding

12:44.066 --> 12:46.510
miracle, of course, he was raised after four days.

12:47.211 --> 12:57.366
And we're told in verse 9 to 11, now, a great many of the Jews knew that he was there, and they came not for Jesus' sake only, but they might also see Lazarus, whom he had raised from the dead.

12:57.406 --> 13:08.082
But the chief priests plotted to put Lazarus to death also, because on account of him, many of the Jews went, or literally, they were going away, and they were believing in Jesus.

13:08.194 --> 13:19.748
And what this is saying is that over a period of weeks, since his miracle, he was being visited by many, many Jews to hear his story and to see him in person.

13:20.109 --> 13:23.293
And Lazarus had been faithfully witnessing to them.

13:23.934 --> 13:34.146
And as a result, many of them were actually leaving the religious leaders and believing in Jesus.

13:34.647 --> 13:37.010
So he is a picture of a witnessing

13:37.154 --> 13:46.645
and he was so effective in his witness that they also plan to kill Lazarus too because he was living proof that Jesus is the Messiah.

13:47.446 --> 13:56.437
But the main focus we want to look at as we look at different pictures of believers is Mary and she is worshiping.

13:58.640 --> 14:05.188
She is a picture of a believer who worships the Lord and what a picture she gives us.

14:06.109 --> 14:06.930
In verse three

14:07.138 --> 14:17.149
John 12.3 it says, then Mary took a pound of very costly oil of spike nard, which as we read in Matthew was in Alabasca flask.

14:17.169 --> 14:25.999
And she anointed the feet of Jesus and wiped his feet with her hair and the house was filled with the fragrance of the oil.

14:26.039 --> 14:32.306
And she is a picture of a true worshipper lavishing all her love

14:32.450 --> 14:33.191
on Christ.

14:33.391 --> 14:36.094
She is extravagant as we're going to see.

14:36.615 --> 14:42.642
She doesn't just, she has got this very expensive jar.

14:42.722 --> 14:46.446
We'll see that it's actually was worth a year's wages.

14:47.307 --> 14:50.872
You know, so we might say 20,000 pounds, 30,000 pounds.

14:50.912 --> 14:52.333
You know, something like this.

14:53.595 --> 14:59.762
And she actually, this was probably her life savings.

15:00.098 --> 15:10.173
You know, she had put her money into this very expensive perfume that had to be brought from India or Tibet.

15:10.794 --> 15:14.399
And this was very valuable, really her life savings.

15:14.900 --> 15:22.671
And what a sensible thing would have been is to, you know, open it and just give a little bit to anoint Jesus with.

15:22.952 --> 15:27.619
This is the kind of perfume that you would keep and use a bit of the time over many years, perhaps.

15:28.660 --> 15:30.002
But instead of that,

15:30.242 --> 15:33.868
she smashed it and she gave Jesus her all.

15:34.248 --> 15:35.651
She withhold nothing.

15:36.632 --> 15:41.120
And this actually brings causes her to be criticized as we're going to see.

15:41.781 --> 15:49.213
But this is a picture of believers worshiping God where they pour their all out for the Lord.

15:49.233 --> 15:50.414
They don't hold back.

15:50.475 --> 15:52.378
They don't measure their love.

15:53.019 --> 15:54.721
We give everything to the Lord.

15:55.362 --> 15:57.586
And in fact, this process

15:57.826 --> 16:12.403
that she acted out is a picture of what should happen in us, because the perfume is like our spirit, our love that is inside us, when Christ has saved us and changed us, you see.

16:12.923 --> 16:23.175
But there is an outward resistance in our soul to give all our love to the Lord.

16:24.256 --> 16:25.938
And something has to be broken.

16:27.010 --> 16:29.173
There needs to be a breaking of our pride.

16:29.634 --> 16:35.863
There needs to be a breaking of that thing that causes us to hold ourselves back, to not give our all.

16:36.384 --> 16:41.031
And in our soul, there's, it's, what you may need called it, the independent soul life.

16:41.452 --> 16:48.242
It's something that resists just abandoning ourselves to God and trusting in God completely.

16:48.354 --> 16:49.555
that had to be broken.

16:49.595 --> 17:00.928
And one of the ways that is broken is Mary was so overwhelmed with God's extravagant love for her that she actually, her pride was broken.

17:01.769 --> 17:13.362
And now she just, like the vase was broken, her pride was broken so that now all the perfume, all the spirit in her was

17:13.826 --> 17:14.407
released.

17:14.767 --> 17:33.073
Let's see that again in verse 3, it says, then Mary took a pound, big quantity of very expensive stuff, a very costly oil of spark nard and anointed the feet of Jesus and wiped his feet with her hair and the house was filled with the fragrance of the oil.

17:34.014 --> 17:42.546
And when we are overwhelmed with the love of Christ for us, we will, our pride is broken and we just

17:42.626 --> 17:43.887
give our all to Him.

17:44.368 --> 17:54.237
And when we do, when our Spirit is released in worship, and then the Spirit of God is released through us, and it fills the whole atmosphere around us.

17:54.958 --> 18:01.764
Our life becomes filled with the fragrance of Jesus, and also we carry that atmosphere with us.

18:02.565 --> 18:05.087
And so notice also Mary was at Jesus' feet.

18:05.107 --> 18:07.810
Whenever we see Mary, she's always at Jesus' feet.

18:08.030 --> 18:12.594
And it's interesting that in rabbis of that time, their followers serve them.

18:12.706 --> 18:17.732
But what they wouldn't do is minister to their feet because that was considered the job of a slave.

18:18.433 --> 18:24.981
And so remember, John the Baptist said, I'm not worthy even to untie Jesus' sandals.

18:25.902 --> 18:30.468
But what Mary is doing at the feet of Jesus is going beyond.

18:31.169 --> 18:37.717
She is actually saying, everything I am, everything I have belongs to Jesus.

18:38.478 --> 18:42.162
And so she is at his feet, worshiping him.

18:42.626 --> 18:46.710
and also she takes her hair.

18:47.150 --> 18:51.495
Now a woman's hair is her glory according to 1 Corinthians 11, 15.

18:51.855 --> 18:57.901
So she is laying her glory at his feet by wiping his feet with her hair.

18:58.502 --> 19:01.224
And so she is giving her all to Jesus.

19:01.264 --> 19:08.231
And that's why Jesus said wherever the gospel is preached, this should be a memorial to her.

19:08.592 --> 19:11.154
First of all, what she did was

19:11.266 --> 19:14.090
as we're going to see, anoint Jesus for burial.

19:14.110 --> 19:21.020
So it was an important part of the story of the lead up to his death and resurrection.

19:21.540 --> 19:27.849
But this is the opening of Passion Week when he was set aside to be the Lamb of God.

19:28.550 --> 19:35.740
But also it's to be mentioned whenever the gospel is preached because that is the desired fruit of the gospel.

19:36.321 --> 19:37.042
You know

19:37.282 --> 19:50.597
when the gospel has truly reached your heart, penetrated your heart, that you are so aware of the extravagant love of Jesus for you because this is what he did for you.

19:50.637 --> 20:01.810
His body was broken and his life and his love, his blood was poured out for you and so that it fills

20:02.466 --> 20:06.050
His presence fills the whole earth so that all people can be saved.

20:06.370 --> 20:16.602
Because Jesus was extravagant in His love for us, then the appropriate response for us is to likewise, like Mary did.

20:16.782 --> 20:17.983
She gives us the example.

20:18.504 --> 20:21.327
Give the Lord Jesus our all in worship.

20:22.248 --> 20:27.694
Has your pride been broken to the place where you are able to give all your love to Jesus?

20:28.535 --> 20:29.376
To like Mary?

20:29.756 --> 20:31.218
To be at His feet?

20:31.362 --> 20:35.467
to worship, to surrender and give Him your all.

20:35.547 --> 20:43.697
Because that is what the gospel should produce in your life if you have truly understood and received it.

20:44.318 --> 20:49.284
Now, let's contrast Mary with Judas, the opposite, who is a counterfeit believer.

20:50.005 --> 20:55.412
And we'll see that his attitude showed that he wasn't a real believer.

20:55.892 --> 21:00.498
In fact, he considered Jesus unworthy of worship.

21:01.026 --> 21:14.606
Verse 4 it says, but one of his disciples, Judas Iscariot, Simon's son, who would betray him, said, why was this fragrant oil not sold for 300 denari and given to the poor?

21:14.926 --> 21:19.533
Now that's 300 days wages, that's like a year's salary.

21:20.314 --> 21:22.638
He said, why didn't she give it to the poor?

21:22.658 --> 21:30.930
And he's basically saying, and in the other gospel it says that why this waste, you have wasted

21:32.482 --> 21:35.005
Thousands of pounds on Jesus.

21:35.085 --> 21:36.947
In other words, Jesus isn't worth it.

21:37.348 --> 21:40.392
It could have been used for the poor, which sounded reasonable.

21:41.553 --> 21:45.257
And actually the other disciples came into agreement with Judas.

21:45.297 --> 21:48.241
They didn't realize he was in a wrong spirit at the time.

21:48.882 --> 21:59.174
And so it explains in verse six, this he said, not that he cared for the poor, but because he was a thief and he had the money box and he used to take what was put in it.

21:59.915 --> 22:02.418
So Judas was motivated by greed.

22:02.946 --> 22:05.009
He said, oh, we ought to give it to the poor.

22:05.049 --> 22:08.675
But his idea was he would, the money could be given to him.

22:09.056 --> 22:09.797
It could be sold.

22:10.538 --> 22:13.002
He would sell it and get the money.

22:13.362 --> 22:17.749
He'd pretend to give it all to the poor, but actually he would take a huge cut for himself.

22:18.911 --> 22:22.296
And they wouldn't realize he'd probably take a quarter of it for himself.

22:22.997 --> 22:26.002
And so it's because he wanted the money.

22:26.402 --> 22:34.893
And he's a picture of someone who looked like he was a Christian, if you like, a follower of Jesus, but actually he was only in it for himself.

22:35.594 --> 22:37.897
He was only in it to get the money and the power.

22:38.238 --> 22:46.729
He thought if Jesus became the kind of political leader and messiah, then he would be one of the top men and he'd have lots of power and wealth.

22:47.190 --> 22:48.151
That's why he was in it.

22:48.772 --> 22:53.138
And that's why, by the way, when Jesus said, actually Mary's anointed me for burial,

22:53.666 --> 22:55.949
Jesus was confirming that he was going to die.

22:56.049 --> 23:02.156
Jesus said, Judas thought, well, that's not what I signed up for.

23:02.456 --> 23:05.059
I signed up so I could become rich and powerful.

23:05.800 --> 23:12.247
And so he thought, well, if Jesus is going to die, I might as well get some kind of money out of this.

23:12.327 --> 23:16.833
And that's why he betrayed Jesus for 30 pieces of silver.

23:16.893 --> 23:21.618
And then I'll be in good standing with the religious authorities and I'll be

23:21.890 --> 23:23.893
I'll be rewarded accordingly.

23:24.254 --> 23:33.408
And so Judas is somebody who looks like they're following Jesus, but they're actually using Jesus for their own ends.

23:34.169 --> 23:44.205
And the moment they have to sacrifice as part of following Jesus, like Mary was willing to sacrifice her life savings to obey God, to honor Jesus.

23:44.746 --> 23:50.194
But when it looked like Judas would have to sacrifice, when it seemed like Jesus was going to die.

23:50.370 --> 23:51.851
He was out of here.

23:52.572 --> 23:55.055
And so he wasn't really a follower of Jesus.

23:55.095 --> 23:56.556
He didn't love him personally.

23:56.936 --> 23:58.198
He was just using him.

23:58.898 --> 24:03.963
And so unbelief will always end up in renunciation of Jesus in the end.

24:04.564 --> 24:12.111
And so he's a picture of someone who wasn't one, didn't have a committed relationship to Jesus.

24:12.512 --> 24:14.073
He was just in it for himself.

24:14.814 --> 24:18.898
Whereas Mary is a picture of a true believer who is

24:19.906 --> 24:22.050
totally devoted to the Lord.

24:22.611 --> 24:37.856
And so the world thinks you waste your time when you spend time worshipping the Lord, or if you spend time in church, or if you spend time at the beginning of each day worshipping God, and your flesh will tell you, it's a waste.

24:38.377 --> 24:40.761
You could be doing something productive with that time.

24:42.063 --> 24:46.290
But what you give to the Lord is never a waste.

24:46.658 --> 24:47.039
All right.

24:47.359 --> 24:49.242
And what Mary did was not wasted.

24:49.522 --> 24:53.388
It was sacrificial, but at number one, it pleased Jesus heart.

24:53.448 --> 24:58.315
Number two, she fulfilled the will of God in anointing him for burial.

24:58.755 --> 25:06.667
And number three, she has now become famous as somebody giving us the example of worshiping God.

25:06.687 --> 25:12.856
So verse seven, it says, Jesus said, let her alone, for she has kept this for the day of my burial.

25:13.797 --> 25:14.418
And what

25:15.074 --> 25:25.149
What Jesus is saying to Judas is, leave her be because she is not to sell it for the poor, but she is actually, she had this for a time.

25:25.189 --> 25:26.371
It was her life savings.

25:26.891 --> 25:31.578
And when she heard Jesus talk about that, he would have to die and rise again.

25:32.139 --> 25:40.672
She then put this savings, this ointment aside for his burial, to anoint him for his burial.

25:41.213 --> 25:44.818
And so, and then of course,

25:44.994 --> 25:51.902
She was obviously led by God not to wait till he actually died, but to actually anoint him right then.

25:51.942 --> 25:54.524
And she obeyed God in that.

25:55.045 --> 26:01.652
And as a result, through her obedience, she was greatly blessed, greatly honored as a result.

26:02.253 --> 26:12.264
And so because she stayed so close to the Lord, always at His feet, she had that spiritual sensitivity to know what to do.

26:12.964 --> 26:14.386
And she poured

26:14.530 --> 26:16.372
her very best out to the Lord.

26:16.793 --> 26:22.259
And what she was actually doing is she was anointing Jesus, the Passover lamb for burial.

26:22.320 --> 26:32.091
And over the next few days, Jesus would start his walk to the cross until he ultimately offered himself up as the Passover lamb.

26:32.112 --> 26:40.562
And then on the last day of the Passion Week, he rose again from the dead, victorious, having accomplished our salvation.

26:41.223 --> 26:42.985
And so the Lord loves you.

26:43.005 --> 26:43.986
He has

26:44.354 --> 26:45.416
been broken for you.

26:45.436 --> 26:52.466
And he has poured out his love and he's poured out his blood and his Holy Spirit.

26:52.967 --> 26:57.093
And now the perfume of his sacrificial offering fills the world.

26:58.054 --> 27:11.794
And now, as you realize he did that for you, out of love for you, our response must be to do the same, to say, to give Jesus our all.

27:12.738 --> 27:17.205
Let the truth, let the revelation of this, break your pride.

27:18.207 --> 27:32.308
The pride that says, oh, I mustn't, you know, the pride that stops you lifting up your hands, the pride that stops you giving your all, shouting your praise to God or lying prostrate on the floor, giving God your worship.

27:32.328 --> 27:36.235
Let that be broken as you realize Jesus gave his all for you.

27:36.615 --> 27:38.879
So you should give your all to him.

27:39.660 --> 27:41.042
Hold nothing back.

27:41.570 --> 27:49.220
be extravagant in your love for God because this is the example that Mary has given us.

27:50.101 --> 27:54.147
And she is to be our example.

27:55.168 --> 28:00.215
But as Jesus said, what she has done is to be a memorial for all those who've heard the gospel.

28:00.735 --> 28:03.479
This is the response God wants from us.

28:04.200 --> 28:08.946
He wants our hearts and he wants all of us that we would be willing to

28:09.090 --> 28:13.180
to give him our all and sacrifice our all if he asks for it.

28:13.882 --> 28:20.899
And so please be inspired by the love and the worship of Mary of Bethany.

28:21.381 --> 28:22.002
God bless you.

